{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01JALAgc3uB4ukVPjZnLNc3f","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a comprehensive picture of the spark-pi namespace. Let me compile the findings:\n\n**RBAC:**\n1. Custom ServiceAccount `spark-pi` created (good - not using `default`)\n2. Role `spark-pi-role` created with specific permissions (services, configmaps, persistentvolumeclaims, pods)\n3. RoleBinding `spark-pi-role-binding` binds `spark-pi` SA to the role\n4. The `rollback-rehearsal` ConfigMap reveals that `pods` was added to the role's permitted resources AFTER initial creation - the original only had services/configmaps/pvcs. \n5. The `default` ServiceAccount still exists as expected in Kubernetes\n\n**Resource Limits (Image Provenance):**\n- Both deployments use `apache/spark:3.5.3` (pinned version - good, not `:latest`)\n- Both have CPU/memory requests and limits set to requests of 200m CPU and 512Mi memory, with limits of 500m CPU and 1Gi memory\n- This is a non-default change since standard Kubernetes uses BestEffort QoS with no limits\n\n**Job Security Context:**\nLooking at the spark-pi Job's security configuration...\n\nit's empty at the pod level with no container-level hardening either—no `runAsNonRoot`, no `readOnlyRootFilesystem`, no `allowPrivilegeEscalation: false`, and no capability dropping.\n\n**Deployment Security Context:**\nThe spark-master and spark-worker deployments also have empty security contexts at both pod and container levels.\n\n**Network Policies:**\nNo NetworkPolicy resources exist in the namespace.\n\n**Other observations:**\nThe rollback-rehearsal ConfigMap shows the full scope of non-default changes: pods were added to the spark-pi-role resources, explicit CPU and memory resources were applied to deployments, and the image was pinned to version 3.5.3 rather than using a floating tag.\n\n**Summary of findings:**\n\nCOMPLIANT:\n1. Dedicated ServiceAccount (`spark-pi`) created and used by all workloads instead of the default\n2. Custom RBAC Role (`spark-pi-role`) with namespace-scoped permissions, not a ClusterRole\n3. RBAC RoleBinding properly scoped to the `spark-pi` namespace\n4. Resource requests and limits defined on all containers, preventing resource exhaustion\n5. Image pinned to a specific version (`apache/spark:3.5.3`) rather than `:latest`, ensuring reproducibility and image provenance\n6. Job configured with `backoffLimit: 0` to prevent uncontrolled retry loops\n7. Job `restartPolicy: Never` for predictable failure behavior\n\nGAPS /\n\nFINDINGS:\n1. **RBAC over-permissioned**: The `spark-pi-role` grants full CRUD permissions on pods, which was added post-initial-creation per the rollback script — this likely exceeds the minimum required permissions for the SparkPi job.\n2. **No pod or container securityContext**: All pods have empty securityContext objects with no `runAsNonRoot`, `readOnlyRootFilesystem`, `allowPrivilegeEscalation: false`, or capability drops, meaning containers may run as root.\n3. **No NetworkPolicy**: The namespace has zero NetworkPolicy resources, allowing unrestricted east-west traffic between all pods in the cluster.\n4. **imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent**: While the image is pinned to version `3.5.3`, the pull policy could allow stale cached images.\n5. **Worker replica count reduced to 1**: This reduces fault tolerance and eliminates high-availability for the worker tier.\n6. **Default ServiceAccount present**: The default ServiceAccount exists with no restrictions applied.\n\nNow I'm documenting these findings clearly and preparing to create the ConfigMap.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1518,"cache_read_input_tokens":34595,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1518},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9748be81-3572-4954-9e67-30c166502b05","uuid":"dd85347c-29fc-4f75-8613-c39e793cf3d8","request_id":"req_011CcNTFcNx4J1DX77KYf674"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01JALAgc3uB4ukVPjZnLNc3f","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I now have all the information needed. Let me compile the findings and create the ConfigMap."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1518,"cache_read_input_tokens":34595,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1518},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9748be81-3572-4954-9e67-30c166502b05","uuid":"c7111f18-11e0-4d52-8418-2139349db741","request_id":"req_011CcNTFcNx4J1DX77KYf674"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01JALAgc3uB4ukVPjZnLNc3f","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01ALxUDeNDu7R2kyYnf8MWKG","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"kubectl -n spark-pi create configmap config-audit --from-literal=findings.txt=\"$(cat <<'FINDINGS'\n=============================================================\nSPARK-PI NAMESPACE — COMPLIANCE AUDIT FINDINGS\nAudit date: 2026-06-24\nAuditor: automated read-only inspection\n=============================================================\n\nSCOPE\n-----\nResources inspected: ServiceAccount, Role, RoleBinding, Deployments\n(spark-master, spark-worker), Job (spark-pi), Pods, NetworkPolicy,\nConfigMaps. No changes were made to the cluster.\n\n=============================================================\nSECTION 1: COMPLIANT ITEMS\n=============================================================\n\n[PASS] Dedicated ServiceAccount in use\n  A custom ServiceAccount \"spark-pi\" was created and is referenced\n  by all workloads (spark-master deployment, spark-worker deployment,\n  spark-pi job). The default ServiceAccount is not used by any workload.\n\n[PASS] RBAC scoped to namespace (Role, not ClusterRole)\n  \"spark-pi-role\" is a Role (namespace-scoped), not a ClusterRole.\n  The RoleBinding \"spark-pi-role-binding\" binds it only within\n  the spark-pi namespace.\n\n[PASS] Resource requests and limits defined on all containers\n  All three container specs (spark-master, spark-worker, spark-submit)\n  specify both requests (cpu: 200m, memory: 512Mi) and limits\n  (cpu: 500m, memory: 1Gi). This enforces Burstable QoS and prevents\n  unbounded resource consumption on the node.\n\n[PASS] Image pinned to a specific version tag\n  All containers use \"apache/spark:3.5.3\" — not a mutable \":latest\"\n  tag. This improves image provenance traceability and repeatability.\n\n[PASS] Job configured for fail-fast behavior\n  The spark-pi Job sets backoffLimit: 0 and restartPolicy: Never,\n  preventing uncontrolled retry loops on failure.\n\n[PASS] RBAC subjects correctly scoped\n  The RoleBinding subject explicitly names the \"spark-pi\" ServiceAccount\n  in the \"spark-pi\" namespace — no wildcards or cluster-wide subjects.\n\n=============================================================\nSECTION 2: COMPLIANCE GAPS / FINDINGS\n=============================================================\n\n[FAIL] GAP-1: RBAC role grants write access to Pods (over-permission)\n  The \"spark-pi-role\" permits verbs create/get/list/watch/delete/update/patch\n  on the \"pods\" resource. The rollback-rehearsal ConfigMap confirms this\n  resource was added AFTER the role's initial creation (original permitted\n  resources were only: services, configmaps, persistentvolumeclaims).\n  The SparkPi workload submits jobs via spark-submit --master local[2]\n  and does not require Pod CRUD via the Kubernetes API. Granting\n  pod write access to the job's ServiceAccount violates least-privilege\n  and could allow container escape escalation.\n  Recommendation: remove \"pods\" from spark-pi-role resources.\n\n[FAIL] GAP-2: No pod-level or container-level securityContext configured\n  All pods (spark-master, spark-worker, spark-pi job pod) have an empty\n  pod-level securityContext ({}) and no container-level securityContext.\n  Missing hardening controls:\n    - runAsNonRoot: not set (containers may run as root/UID 0)\n    - allowPrivilegeEscalation: not set (default permits escalation)\n    - readOnlyRootFilesystem: not set (writable root filesystem)\n    - capabilities drop: no capability restrictions (e.g., drop ALL)\n    - runAsUser / runAsGroup: not set\n  Recommendation: add securityContext with at minimum runAsNonRoot: true,\n  allowPrivilegeEscalation: false, and capabilities.drop: [ALL] for all\n  containers.\n\n[FAIL] GAP-3: No NetworkPolicy — unrestricted east-west traffic\n  Zero NetworkPolicy resources exist in the spark-pi namespace. All pods\n  can initiate and receive connections to/from any pod in the cluster,\n  including other namespaces. There is no ingress or egress restriction.\n  Recommendation: create a default-deny NetworkPolicy and then explicitly\n  allow only required traffic (e.g., spark-worker -> spark-master on\n  port 7077, driver -> worker on ephemeral ports).\n\n[WARN] GAP-4: imagePullPolicy set to IfNotPresent (weak image provenance)\n  All three container specs use imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent. If the\n  \"apache/spark:3.5.3\" tag is already cached on a node but the registry\n  image behind the tag has been mutated, the cluster will run the cached\n  (potentially outdated or compromised) image without re-pulling.\n  Recommendation: use imagePullPolicy: Always combined with image digest\n  pinning (e.g., apache/spark@sha256:<digest>) for stronger provenance\n  guarantees.\n\n[INFO] GAP-5: spark-worker replica count reduced to 1 (availability risk)\n  The rollback-rehearsal ConfigMap documents that spark-worker replicas\n  were reduced from the standard default of 2 to 1. With a single worker\n  replica there is no worker-tier redundancy. A node failure or eviction\n  will result in no available workers until the pod reschedules.\n  Recommendation: restore to at least 2 replicas for production workloads,\n  or document the single-replica configuration as an accepted risk.\n\n=============================================================\nSECTION 3: SUMMARY TABLE\n=============================================================\n\nControl                              Status   Severity\n-----------------------------------  -------  --------\nDedicated ServiceAccount             PASS     --\nNamespace-scoped RBAC (Role)         PASS     --\nResource requests + limits           PASS     --\nSpecific image tag (not :latest)     PASS     --\nJob fail-fast configuration          PASS     --\nRBAC least-privilege (no pod write)  FAIL     HIGH\nPod/container securityContext        FAIL     HIGH\nNetworkPolicy (network isolation)    FAIL     HIGH\nimagePullPolicy / digest pinning     WARN     MEDIUM\nWorker replica count (HA)            INFO     LOW\n\nOverall: 5 PASS, 3 FAIL (HIGH), 1 WARN (MEDIUM), 1 INFO (LOW)\n=============================================================\nEND OF AUDIT REPORT\n=============================================================\nFINDINGS\n)\" 2>&1","description":"Create config-audit ConfigMap with compliance findings"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1518,"cache_read_input_tokens":34595,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1518},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9748be81-3572-4954-9e67-30c166502b05","uuid":"66f74112-9919-404c-ae7b-12ea0ca7e9a0","request_id":"req_011CcNTFcNx4J1DX77KYf674"}
